cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.Distributed, cs.SY, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the implementation of atomic registers on top of a crash-prone asynchronous message-passing system, which falls under the domain of distributed computing. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an algorithm for implementing a single-writer multi-reader atomic register, which involves designing a data structure and algorithmic techniques. 
3. cs.Distributed - The paper deals with the implementation of atomic registers in a distributed system, which is the primary focus of this sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the design and implementation of a system for achieving atomicity in a distributed environment, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper presents an algorithm for implementing atomic registers, which involves programming techniques and language constructs.
